-- Fersa Energias, Lafarge, Prismaflex, Volkswagen: Europe Equity Preview
-- Caroline Dye
-- 2010-07-07T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/fersa-lafarge-prismaflex-volkswagen-may-move-europe-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  
 The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  gained 2.6 percent to 242.76.
The  Stoxx 50 Index  rose 2.6 percent to 2,348.08. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index , a benchmark for nations using the euro, advanced 2.8
percent to 2,578.69.  
 Fersa Energias Renovables SA  (FRS SM): The Barcelona-based
clean energy developer said it won a contract to build and
operate the first wind farm in Montenegro.  
 Lafarge SA  (LG FP): The world’s largest cement maker, sold
$550 million of five-year notes, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg. The 5.5 percent debt yields 375 basis points more
than similar-maturity Treasuries, Bloomberg data show.  
 Prismaflex International  (PRS FP): The advertising company
said the majority of its bankers agreed to waive a clause that
would mean the company defaulted on a structured loan for the
year ended March 31.  
 Volkswagen AG  (VOW GR): Europe’s largest carmaker plans to
invest as much as $1 billion in Mexico over the next three
years, which will likely include a new engine plant, production
chief  Jochem Heizmann  said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:  Caroline Dye  in New York
at   cdye@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        